            <title>[CXF-2700] Invalid method is used to get the value of the xml:lang attribute in the SOAP1.2 Text Element</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2700</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The class org.apache.cxf.binding.soap.interceptor.Soap12FaultOutInterceptor.Soap12FaultOutInterceptorInternal uses java.util.Locale#getDisplayLanguage() for determining the value of the xml:lang attribute of the SOAP Text Element. To get a language code, the proper method should be java.util.Locale#getLanguage().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this is fixed, you can set your default locale language to the xml:lang attribute by creating a non-empty resource &apos;org/apache/cxf/binding/soap/interceptor/Messages_&amp;lt;language code&amp;gt;.properties&apos; in the classpath. Currently there is no way to set the value other than &apos;en&apos; (default value).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
